                    <span>These translations  sadly do not give me essence . It is often however, instructive for a little money(this book is unbelievably well priced) to compare for yourself the entries of this book( the sutras are all numbered so its easy to do) with another translation.You owe it to yourself to own for instance the Penguin Dhammapada.As for this Muller copy,If you are a scholar of asian and european languages and seek fine contexts,it may well be educational . My scholarship is very  sadly limited,but my love is very unlimited,so I'm moved by words that speak to my inmost being.</span>
                  
              
